  "incidentId": "22d3c063-0277-4754-8b84-da553856579a",
  "final": {
    "status": "awaiting_approval",
    "rootCause": "The root cause is a combination of insufficient service capacity and a fragile connection pool design. The order-service runs with only 2 ECS tasks, which is undersized for the current load. Under high request volume, the fixed-size database connection pool (with no adaptive backoff) became fully exhausted — all connections checked out, none available for new requests. Because the code does not implement backoff or circuit-breaking on checkout failure, requests fail fast and pile up, preventing the pool from recovering. The sustained >90% CPU confirms the tasks are maxed out. No recent deployment changes rule out a code regression; this is a capacity and architectural resilience issue.",
    "remCount": 1
  }
